pos_mean_info_list.mean: 假定的；被信以为真的；想象上的

word_mean_info__list.difference: 侧重以过去经验或根据现实的某些感觉把某事认定为是事实。
常用词，意义较广泛，指缺乏确切事实，根据一些现象进行的推测，也可指为论证而提出合乎逻辑推理的某种假定，有时仅表示自己的意见。
常用词，指毫无根据仅凭个人主观臆断或碰运气的猜测。
指为证实一个理论的正确性而进行的假设。
指有很少或完全无根据的武断推测或不合逻辑的推理。

word_group.brief_definition: 应该, 应该如此, 被期望

bilingual.source: Let's suppose that he is telling the truth.
bilingual.target: 让我们假设他说的是真的。

bilingual.source: Suppose you had one wish, what would it be?
bilingual.target: 假设你有一个愿望，那会是什么？

bilingual.source: Suppose you win the lottery, what would you do?
bilingual.target: 假设你中了彩票，你会做什么？

bilingual.source: Suppose the weather is bad, let's stay at home.
bilingual.target: 假设天气不好，我们就待在家里吧。

bilingual.source: Suppose we leave now, will we make it on time?
bilingual.target: 假设我们现在出发，我们能准时到达吗？

bilingual.source: Suppose she doesn't come, what will be our plan B?
bilingual.target: 假设她不来，我们的备用计划是什么？

bilingual.source: Suppose he already knows the news, what will he do?
bilingual.target: 假设他已经知道了这个消息，他会怎么做？

bilingual.source: Suppose we have enough time, we can finish this project.
bilingual.target: 假设我们有足够的时间，我们可以完成这个项目。

bilingual.source: Suppose you are the boss, how would you handle this problem?
bilingual.target: 假设你是老板，你会怎么处理这个问题？

bilingual.source: Suppose you are free tomorrow, we can go to the movies together.
bilingual.target: 假设你明天有空，我们可以一起去看电影。

list.abstract: suppose（英[səˈpəʊz]，美[səˈpoʊz]），英文单词，词性为动词，译为认为；料想；估计。短语搭配有be supposed to（应该）。例句为“Let's suppose you want to be singer.（让我们假设你想成为歌手。）” 该单词及物动词类近义词为expect、have、count，不及物动词类近义词为believe、imagine，同根名词为supposition、supposal。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, let's just suppose for a second that she's on a plane to Cabo. What then?
yingyinNormal.zh: 假设她现在坐在一架去往卡波的飞机上，然后呢？

yingyinNormal.en: So what? Look, okay, suppose we were a divorced couple. And I got custody of the kid, right?
yingyinNormal.zh: 那又怎样？听着，假设我们是离婚夫妻，我取得孩子的监护权。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay. Well, Monica, suppose one of your special tickets wins? How are you gonna feel when you win the lottery and lose all your friends?
yingyinNormal.zh: 好了，莫妮卡，假设你的彩票中奖了怎么办？你觉得中了彩票，失去了朋友又怎样？

yingyinNormal.en: I suppose you know why I've come.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你知道我为什么来这儿吗。

yingyinNormal.en: What exactly are you suppose to be?
yingyinNormal.zh: 那你到底是什么呢？

yingyinNormal.en: I suppose. I do miss whistling, though.
yingyinNormal.zh: 差不多吧，尽管我很怀念口哨。

yingyinNormal.en: I suppose you want the sword back. Keep it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我猜您想收回这柄剑。你留着罢。

yingyinNormal.en: If you so stipulate, I suppose that's true.
yingyinNormal.zh: 既然你们如此坚决，我认为那只可能是真的。

yingyinNormal.en: You're a lucky man, Jack. Yes, I suppose I'm.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你很幸运，杰克。我是挺幸运的。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm sure you'll find somebody else. I suppose.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我相信你一定会找到合适的人选。希望吧。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, I suppose I could poison Kripke. No. No.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，那我该给克瑞普克下毒。不！

yingyinNormal.en: It is a small kind of accomplishment, I suppose.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这也是种小技艺，我想。

yingyinNormal.en: I suppose cellists must go to a lot of concerts.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我猜大提琴家要去很多音乐会。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, I suppose we can't all be penguins, can we?
yingyinNormal.zh: 那，我想我们不可能都成为企鹅，你说呢？

yingyinNormal.en: I suppose you know my grandmother agrees with you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我想你知道奶奶赞同你的观点。

yingyinNormal.en: And you're aware, I suppose, that our Lord was Jewish?
yingyinNormal.zh: 那你也应该知道，我们的国王也是犹太人。

yingyinNormal.en: Yes, I suppose you're right. Well, he knew them better.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你说得对，他更了解他们。

yingyinNormal.en: Your daughter, I suppose she talks and eats and everything?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你女儿一切都好吧？

yingyinNormal.en: I suppose this means the sheriff wasn't an isolated incident.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这说明治安官的事不是个别事件。

yingyinNormal.en: Suppose the baby looks like you and people in the village notice? Suppose you talk?
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果孩子长得像你，村里的人注意到了？如果你不小心泄了密呢？

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

adv. 一般说来；根据推测；据称；可能

word_family.mean: v. 认为；料想；估计；必须做；假定；认为应该；猜想；建议；要求以…为前提条件；需以…为条件

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Suppose</highlight> you are organizing an online meeting.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 假设你正在组织一个在线会议。

examination_example.sentence: In contrast, <highlight>suppose</highlight> you give a reasonable argument: that full-time workers should not have to live in poverty.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 相比之下，假设你给出了一个合理的论点: 全职工人不应该生活在贫困中。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Suppose</highlight> you are a librarian in your university.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 假设你是大学的图书管理员。

sense_info_list.en: be required to do something because of the position one is in or an agreement one has made

examination_example.sentence: PreCheck is <highlight>supposed</highlight> to be a win-win for travelers and the TSA.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 预检应该是旅行者和运输安全管理局的双赢。

examination_example.sentence: Researchers measured people's cortisol and found it higher at what is <highlight>supposed</highlight> to be a place of refuge.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 研究者对人们的皮质醇进行了检测，结果发现在人们普遍认为是避风港的环境中，皮质醇的含量更高。

examination_example.sentence: At work, people know what they're <highlight>supposed</highlight> to be doing: working, making money, doing the tasks they have to do.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在工作中，人们知道他们应该做什么: 工作，赚钱，做他们必须做的任务。

sense_info_list.en: assume that something is the case on the basis of evidence or probability but without proof or certain knowledge

<highlight>考纲释义</highlight>

<highlight>考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2016-2023年51套试卷，包括阅读、听力、翻译等所有题型。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2016-2023年8年间全六级试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

word_family.mean: v. 认为；料想；估计；必须做；假定；认为应该；猜想；建议；要求以…为前提条件；需以…为条件

sense_info_list.en: be required to do something because of the position one is in or an agreement one has made

examination_example.sentence: What is a manager <highlight>supposed</highlight> to do to enable workers to do a better job?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 管理者应该做什么才能让员工做得更好？

examination_example.sentence: An exit interview is <highlight>supposed</highlight> to be private, but often isn't.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 离职面谈本应是私密的，但往往不是这样。

examination_example.sentence: This was the first recorded death involving a car which was <highlight>supposed</highlight> to be fully autonomous.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这是第一次有记录的涉及全自动驾驶汽车的死亡事件。

sense_info_list.en: assume that something is the case on the basis of evidence or probability but without proof or certain knowledge

examination_example.sentence: Genetic differences between students are far greater than <highlight>supposed</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 学生之间的基因差异比想象的要大得多。

examination_example.sentence: In honor of the poem's publication on May 24,1830, here's more about the <highlight>supposed</highlight> author's life.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 为了纪念这首诗于1830年5月24日出版，以下是有关作者生平的更多信息。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Suppose</highlight> we want to compare the economic welfare of citizens of the U.S. and France in 2005.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 假设我们比较2005年美国和法国公民的经济福利。

word_usage.usage: suppose后不能直接跟动词不定式。suppose后可加that引导的从句，且句中that可省略。
suppose是表示思想状态的动词，通常不用于进行体。

suppose引导否定意义的宾语从句时，须使用转移否定结构。如：
I don't suppose I will be here tomorrow. 
我想我明天不会在这里。

examination_example.sentence: Under the old system in America, a mother was <highlight>supposed</highlight> to stay home and take care of her children.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在美国古老的制度下，母亲应该呆在家里照顾孩子。

examination_example.sentence: Taylor was <highlight>supposed</highlight> to be able to learn from the messages she received.
examination_example.sentence_trans: Taylor 应该能够从她收到的信息中学习。

examination_example.sentence: Before we collectively tear our hair out—how are we <highlight>supposed</highlight> to find our way in a landscape this confusing?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在我们集体焦虑之前—我们应该如何在如此混乱的环境中找到自己的路？

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Suppose</highlight> you have just participated in a school project of collecting used books on campus.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 假设你刚刚参加了一个学校收集校园旧书的项目。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Suppose</highlight> your university student union is planning to hold a speech contest.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 假设你所在大学的学生会计划举办一场演讲比赛。

examination_example.sentence: The city was <highlight>supposed</highlight> to be a hub for global companies, with employees from all over the world. But that's not how it has turned out.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 松岛新城原本被设想为跨国企业的聚集地，汇集来自世界各地的员工，但结果并非如此。

word_usage.usage:
suppose意为“猜想，料想；认为”时，通常有以下几种用法：
①跟从句，suppose后面的宾语从句的否定往往转移到主句上来。如：
I don't suppose he can finish the work on time, can he？
我想他无法按时完成工作，他能吗？
②跟带不定式的复合结构（不定式主要为to be）suppose sb./sth.to be+形容词/名词：
What makes you suppose him to be connected with them？ 
什么事让你认为他和他们有关系？
③常用于被动结构中：
He was supposed to be an expert in the field.
他被认为是这一领域的专家。
④be supposed to do sth.意为“应该”，如：
Everyone is supposed to wear a seat belt in the car.
车里每个人都应该系好安全带。

word_usage.usage: suppose后不能直接跟动词不定式。suppose后可加that引导的从句，且句中that可省略。
suppose是表示思想状态的动词，通常不用于进行体。

suppose引导否定意义的宾语从句时，须使用转移否定结构。如：
I don't suppose I will be here tomorrow. 
我想我明天不会在这里。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 指在某一前提条件下或根据已有知识、信息等进行推测，有时用于表达意见。
常用词，指毫无根据仅凭个人主观臆断或碰运气的猜测。
